{"title":"TRP Trail EVO and Slate EVO get full EVO treatment for better, more affordable braking","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/08/23/trp-trail-evo-and-slate-evo-get-full-evo-treatment-for-better-more-affordable-braking/","date":1629745865000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><p>TRP has been steadily improving their brakes, and more riders are taking notice. At the high end, their DH-R EVO brakes have received <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2020/12/09/review-trps-dh-r-evo-brakes-offer-predictable-modulation-and-a-forceful-bite/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">excellent reviews</a> for offering plenty of useable power. Now, that same EVO update is being applied to their Trail and Slate brakes for more affordable brake systems with their best performance yet.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/23145156/TRP-Evo.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/23145156/TRP-Evo.jpg?ezimgfmt=rs:484x331/rscb28/ng:webp/ngcb28\" alt=\"\" width=\"950\" height=\"650\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/23145156/TRP-Evo.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 950w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/23145156/TRP-Evo-297x203.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/23145156/TRP-Evo-800x547.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/23145156/TRP-Evo-120x82.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/23145156/TRP-Evo-768x525.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/0