il-EVO_EVOlution-Continues-Info-Flyer-copy-672x420.jpg 672w\"></a></p><p>The Trail EVO is apparently an evolution of the Quadiem, and should be a great brake for aggressive Trail, Enduro, and E-MTB riders. Offering a full 360Â° oil path around all four pistons in the caliper (same caliper as the DH-R EVO), the Trail EVO reduces the chance of brake fade. Trail EVOs are priced at $209.99 per wheel without rotors.</p><p>Both are in stock and available for purchase directly from TRP or through your local bike shop.</p><p><a href=\"https://trpcycling.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><em>trpcycling.com</em></a></p></div></div>","author":"Zach Overholt","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"b7771f36b900890fb0d51f43907e717548c470a8cad93f30dfc25375afb8e8f6","category":"Cycling"}